  description: 'In the summer of 1908, an Italian archaeologist uncovered a small clay disc in the ruins of a Minoan palace on Crete. Covered in 241 mysterious symbols stamped into the clay with individual punches — a technique that would not be reinvented for three thousand years — the Phaistos Disc has defied every attempt at decipherment. Accused of being a forgery, claimed as a prayer, a calendar, a game board, and an adventure story, the disc remains the most famous unsolved puzzle in archaeology. This is the story of its discovery, the obsession it has inspired, and the silence it refuses to break.',
